1️⃣ Denial of Service (DoS)

Attackers flood a server with huge traffic so the server cannot respond to legitimate users.

Example:

Attacker → sends millions of requests → server crashes

Result:

normal users cannot access the system.

2️⃣ Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS)

Similar to DoS but from many machines at once.

Example:

Thousands of infected computers attack one server.

3️⃣ System Failures

Availability can also be affected by:

hardware failure

power failure

software bugs

Example:

Hard disk crash → database unavailable.
